As your Inspector, I have "Red-Teamed" the Section 3 ‚Äî Pipeline you provided. Here are two optimizations to prevent bottlenecks:
1. The "Hallucination Check" Gap
- Risk: ChatGPT (The Builder) is excellent at sounding confident but can hallucinate case law or local rules.
- Fix: In Step G (Inspector), specifically prompt me to: "Verify the logic of the cited legal principles." (Note: I cannot browse live dockets, but I can verify if a legal theory sounds sound or fabricated).
1. The Feedback Loop
- Risk: If I provide heavy revisions, sending it back to ChatGPT (Builder) can sometimes dilute the specific legal nuances I added.
- Fix: If the revisions are substantive, the Strategist (You) should integrate my revisions directly into the final document, rather than asking the Builder to re-draft, to ensure the "sharp edges" of the argument remain intact.
